        "faqs": [
          {
            "question": "What is trenchless sewer repair?",
            "answer": "<a href='/specialty/sewer-line-services/trenchless-sewer-repair'><strong>Trenchless sewer repair</strong></a> is a minimally invasive method of repairing or replacing sewer lines without digging large trenches. We use techniques like pipe lining and <a href='/specialty/sewer-line-services/pipe-bursting-lining'><strong>pipe bursting</strong></a> to restore your <a href='/residential/drain/sewer-line'><strong>sewer line</strong></a> with minimal disruption to your property."
          },
          {
            "question": "How does infrared leak detection work?",
            "answer": "Infrared cameras detect temperature differences behind walls, floors, and ceilings caused by moisture from hidden leaks. This allows us to locate leaks precisely without cutting into your walls or floors."
          },
          {
            "question": "Is hydro jetting safe for older pipes?",
            "answer": "Our technicians assess the condition of your pipes before recommending <a href='/specialty/hydro-jetting/high-pressure-drain-cleaning'><strong>hydro jetting</strong></a>. For older or fragile pipes, we may suggest alternative cleaning methods to avoid damage."
          },
          {
            "question": "Do you offer 24/7 emergency plumbing?",
